description.narrative: Emergency-affected people are provided with lifesaving WASH interventions, especially women and girls., which contributes to Children In Urban Settings / Local Governance, Sanitation, Water, Water (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2020, increased numbers of people, especially girls and women, socially excluded groups and others in vulnerable situations, are healthy and live in resilient communities, access affordable and equitable WASH services and abandon open defecation

description.narrative: Through UNICEF's lifesaving actions, 1,918,825 1,782,025 people (5256.4% of target) accessed safe drinking water, 273,514 266,954 (24.525% of target) with appropriate sanitation and 1,723,5452,854,544 (57.495% of target) reached with hygiene promotion as well as provision of means to practice proper hygiene including menstrual hygiene kits for women and teenage girls. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
